                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1348">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/123.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Special
                        Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 15, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Señor Juan Francisco de Cardenas, Secretary of Spanish Legation, Habana, has been
                    ordered by his Government to El Paso, where he will probably arrive to-morrow or
                    the day after. He will later <pb facs="0905" n="789" xml:id="pg_789"/> visit
                    certain points in Mexico on special mission regarding protection Spanish
                    subjects in that country. The Department would greatly appreciate any courtesies
                    and assistance you could extend to him. Please telegraph when he will leave for
                    Mexico and what points he will visit in order that our consular officers may be
                    instructed to facilitate his mission. Confer with Mr. Cobb, Collector of
                    Customs, and ask his cooperation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
